"Observatory on the 30th floor" -the entire city of Shimonoseki.

31
00:03:00,345 --> 00:03:02,944
Wow, this is great.

32
00:03:02,945 --> 00:03:04,344
Look over there,

33
00:03:04,345 --> 00:03:06,144
"Ganryu Island" -that's Ganryu Island,

34
00:03:06,145 --> 00:03:08,144
that's where Musashi Miyamoto and Kojiro Sasaki fought that famous battle.

35
00:03:08,145 --> 00:03:10,844
It's smaller than I expected.

36
00:03:10,845 --> 00:03:14,244
Hey, Ran. Isn't that Kyushu over there?

37
00:03:14,245 --> 00:03:15,544
Yes, it is.

38
00:03:15,545 --> 00:03:19,744
The Kanmon Strait is pretty narrow, isn't it?

39
00:03:19,745 --> 00:03:23,744
Says here the narrowest area's only 700 m.

40
00:03:23,745 --> 00:03:26,344
If you ran across it, you'd reach Kyushu in five minutes.

41
00:03:26,345 --> 00:03:29,545
Oh for goodness sakes, how are you going to run across the ocean?

42
00:03:30,545 --> 00:03:32,145
Really?

43
00:03:35,145 --> 00:03:37,644
Dad, you're so embarrassing.

44
00:03:37,645 --> 00:03:40,845
He's right, you can run across.

45
00:03:42,045 --> 00:03:45,744
Are you talking about that bridge?

46
00:03:45,745 --> 00:03:49,444
No, that's the Kanmon Bridge, it's only for cars.

47
00:03:49,445 --> 00:03:51,944
But there's an underwater tunnel.

48
00:03:51,945 --> 00:03:55,044
"Keisuke Otsubo, Toru Akitaya" -directly under it for human traffic.

49
00:03:55,045 --> 00:03:57,944
It's nicknamed "The People's Tunnel".

50
00:03:57,945 --> 00:04:00,844
Gee, you sure know a lot.

51
00:04:00,845 --> 00:04:02,944
We grew up in this neighborhood.

52
00:04:02,945 --> 00:04:04,244
No wonder.

53
00:04:04,245 --> 00:04:05,844
It can't be.

54
00:04:05,845 --> 00:04:08,645
"Eiko Nojima, Akane Isaka" -Aren't you Kogoro Mouri?

55
00:04:11,845 --> 00:04:14,244
Yes, I am.

56
00:04:14,245 --> 00:04:15,844
I knew it.

57
00:04:15,845 --> 00:04:19,045
He's that famous private detective.

58
00:04:21,445 --> 00:04:23,644
My name's Akitaya.

59
00:04:23,645 --> 00:04:24,944
I'm Keisuke Otsubo.

60
00:04:24,945 --> 00:04:26,544
I'm Akane Isaka.

61
00:04:26,545 --> 00:04:28,144
I'm Eiko Nojima.

62
00:04:28,145 --> 00:04:30,744
We're all fans of yours, Mr. Mouri.

63
00:04:30,745 --> 00:04:31,944
Aren't we? Aren't we?

64
00:04:31,945 --> 00:04:34,044
-We sure are. -Yes.

65
00:04:34,045 --> 00:04:36,145
Really?

66
00:04:38,645 --> 00:04:42,544
Yeah, everyone knows Kogoro only for his name and his face,

67
00:04:42,545 --> 00:04:44,244
which means...

68
00:04:44,245 --> 00:04:46,544
If it's not an imposition,

69
00:04:46,545 --> 00:04:49,144
would you join us for dinner?

70
00:04:49,145 --> 00:04:52,744
Great idea. We'd really like to hear your stories.

71
00:04:52,745 --> 00:04:54,344
I knew it.

72
00:04:54,345 --> 00:04:56,144
Well...

73
00:04:56,145 --> 00:04:58,044
They were nice enough to offer,

74
00:04:58,045 --> 00:04:59,744
shall we accept?

75
00:04:59,745 --> 00:05:01,444
Besides, they're locals so they probably know

76
00:05:01,445 --> 00:05:03,744
where the good restaurants are.

77
00:05:03,745 --> 00:05:05,244
We were raised here

78
00:05:05,245 --> 00:05:08,644
but she and I have been living in Tokyo since college.

79
00:05:08,645 --> 00:05:11,244
How do you all know each other?

80
00:05:11,245 --> 00:05:14,644
We were all in the same class in high school.

81
00:05:14,645 --> 00:05:18,144
High school classmates?

82
00:05:18,145 --> 00:05:19,944
That's so nice.

83
00:05:19,945 --> 00:05:21,744
12 years have passed since you graduated

84
00:05:21,745 --> 00:05:23,544
but you're all still so close.

85
00:05:23,545 --> 00:05:25,244
"Strait Dream Square" -I guess it's because

86
00:05:25,245 --> 00:05:27,844
we all have such different personalities.

87
00:05:27,845 --> 00:05:30,144
I am confident of my ability

88
00:05:30,145 --> 00:05:32,344
but not very smart.

89
00:05:32,345 --> 00:05:35,044
Otsubo's smart but he's a coward.

90
00:05:35,045 --> 00:05:36,844
You've got some nerve.

91
00:05:36,845 --> 00:05:40,644
Akane's smart too but she's pretty mean.

92
00:05:40,645 --> 00:05:41,745
You've got some nerve.

93
00:05:43,245 --> 00:05:46,445
Eiko's sweet but shy.

94
00:05:47,945 --> 00:05:50,644
Actually, there used to be one more in our group.

95
00:05:50,645 --> 00:05:52,844
Another close friend of ours.

96
00:05:52,845 --> 00:05:54,344
Another member?

97
00:05:54,345 --> 00:05:56,044
His name was Hondo,

98
00:05:56,045 --> 00:05:59,944
he could draw really well, he wanted to go to an art college.

99
00:05:59,945 --> 00:06:01,145
But...

100
00:06:03,645 --> 00:06:06,044
In our senior year of high school,

101
00:06:06,045 --> 00:06:08,344
he went to the Kanmon Bridge

102
00:06:08,345 --> 00:06:09,845
and killed himself.

103
00:06:11,045 --> 00:06:12,745
He committed suicide.

104
00:06:14,445 --> 00:06:16,144
I see, he was talented but he probably felt

105
00:06:16,145 --> 00:06:18,044
he'd already given it all he had and nothing left.

106
00:06:18,045 --> 00:06:19,345
You're wrong.

107
00:06:21,745 --> 00:06:22,945
His dream...

108
00:06:24,345 --> 00:06:26,444
His dream was taken from him.

109
00:06:26,445 --> 00:06:28,444
His dream?

110
00:06:28,445 --> 00:06:30,844
He broke his arm.

111
00:06:30,845 --> 00:06:33,845
And it didn't heal right.

112
00:06:36,445 --> 00:06:39,044
I see.

113
00:06:39,045 --> 00:06:43,444
Yesterday was his 13th memorial service.

114
00:06:43,445 --> 00:06:45,244
So that's why you all came from Tokyo.

115
00:06:45,245 --> 00:06:47,544
Well, that was part of the reason.

116
00:06:47,545 --> 00:06:50,344
These two wanted to make an announcement to Eiko and me.

117
00:06:50,345 --> 00:06:53,145
It seems they've gotten engaged.

118
00:06:54,845 --> 00:06:58,044
That's wonderful. Congratulations.

119
00:06:58,045 --> 00:07:02,544
Well, I realized one day that she was the only single one left.

120
00:07:02,545 --> 00:07:03,844
How dare you!

121
00:07:03,845 --> 00:07:06,745
I'm marrying you only because I feel sorry for you.

122
00:07:07,745 --> 00:07:09,944
I think you two make a great couple.

123
00:07:09,945 --> 00:07:11,444
So do I.

124
00:07:11,445 --> 00:07:13,045
-You've got to be kidding. -You've got to be kidding.

125
00:07:14,445 --> 00:07:15,845
Hey, come on.

126
00:07:22,945 --> 00:07:25,844
Conan, look over there. It's so cute.

127
00:07:25,845 --> 00:07:27,545
It's a cetacean.

128
00:07:31,745 --> 00:07:34,445
Well, I see you're all together.

129
00:07:37,445 --> 00:07:39,645
-Hario. -Hario...

130
00:07:40,845 --> 00:07:44,244
Akitaya, I want to talk to you alone,

131
00:07:44,245 --> 00:07:46,445
but I guess this is a bad time.

132
00:07:47,445 --> 00:07:50,244
I'll be here for three to four days,

133
00:07:50,245 --> 00:07:51,745
I'll see you later.

134
00:07:53,545 --> 00:07:56,044
Who was that man?

135
00:07:56,045 --> 00:07:57,544
That's Seiji Hario.

136
00:07:57,545 --> 00:07:59,744
He was also one of our classmates.

137
00:07:59,745 --> 00:08:01,044
Him too?

138
00:08:01,045 --> 00:08:03,944
I wonder what he came back for anyway?

139
00:08:03,945 --> 00:08:06,444
Probably for the memorial service.

140
00:08:06,445 --> 00:08:08,444
Maybe he feels responsible?

141
00:08:08,445 --> 00:08:10,244
What do you mean?

142
00:08:10,245 --> 00:08:11,544
It's that creep's fault.

143
00:08:11,545 --> 00:08:15,144
He's the one who broke Hondo's arm 12 years ago.

144
00:08:15,145 --> 00:08:17,345
He's the one?

145
00:08:18,345 --> 00:08:22,744
I'm sorry, I have to excuse myself.

146
00:08:22,745 --> 00:08:24,745
I think I've worn myself out. I'm going home.

147
00:08:25,745 --> 00:08:27,244
I'm terribly sorry.

148
00:08:27,245 --> 00:08:30,344
I promise to be there for dinner though.

149
00:08:30,345 --> 00:08:31,845
Excuse me.

150
00:08:37,445 --> 00:08:39,244
I hope she's alright.

151
00:08:39,245 --> 00:08:40,944
She didn't look very good.

152
00:08:40,945 --> 00:08:43,945
Hondo was Eiko's boyfriend.

153
00:08:45,645 --> 00:08:47,044
I guess she can't forget him.

154
00:08:47,045 --> 00:08:50,444
She's still in love with Hondo.

155
00:08:50,445 --> 00:08:53,144
That's why she's still single.

156
00:08:53,145 --> 00:08:55,445
It's been 12 years already.

157
00:09:01,145 --> 00:09:03,944
Is Akitaya married?

158
00:09:03,945 --> 00:09:05,144
No.

159
00:09:05,145 --> 00:09:06,344
Why?

160
00:09:06,345 --> 00:09:08,645
I just was just curious.

161
00:09:14,245 --> 00:09:16,344
So we'll see you all later for dinner.

162
00:09:16,345 --> 00:09:18,645
Yes, please enjoy yourselves.

163
00:09:19,645 --> 00:09:21,844
Since the olden days,

164
00:09:21,845 --> 00:09:24,844
"Port of Shimonoseki International Terminal" -Shimonoseki has a history

165
00:09:24,845 --> 00:09:26,844
of being a port city open to foreign ships.

166
00:09:26,845 --> 00:09:28,444
Really?

167
00:09:28,445 --> 00:09:29,644
Look, Conan.

168
00:09:29,645 --> 00:09:32,544
Doesn't this place look like the Dragon King's palace?

169
00:09:32,545 --> 00:09:34,145
"Akama Shrine" -Yeah, you're right.

170
00:09:38,245 --> 00:09:41,144
"Kanmon Bridge."

171
00:09:41,145 --> 00:09:44,545
Boy, this sure is a big bridge.

172
00:09:45,745 --> 00:09:47,744
"Entrance Human Tunnel" -Look, that must be the tunnel.

173
00:09:47,745 --> 00:09:49,744
"(Shimonoseki side)" -Mr. Akitaya told us about.

174
00:09:49,745 --> 00:09:51,745
-Let's go inside. -Okay.

175
00:09:55,845 --> 00:09:58,844
"Human Tunnel B3 (Shimonoseki side)"

176
00:09:58,845 --> 00:10:01,644
"Moji"

177
00:10:01,645 --> 00:10:03,644
I wonder if there's a possibility this place might spring a leak.

178
00:10:03,645 --> 00:10:05,744
I mean, we are underwater.

179
00:10:05,745 --> 00:10:08,645
Oh for goodness sakes, dad, don't worry.

180
00:10:12,645 --> 00:10:16,445
"Yamaguchi Prefecture" "Fukuoka Prefecture."

181
00:10:19,545 --> 00:10:23,544
Look at me. I'm standing in two prefectures at the same time.

182
00:10:23,545 --> 00:10:24,745
Peace.

183
00:10:27,245 --> 00:10:31,445
"Shimonoseki."

184
00:10:32,445 --> 00:10:34,844
Can you believe this?

185
00:10:34,845 --> 00:10:38,544
We just walked across the Kanmon Strait.

186
00:10:38,545 --> 00:10:39,645
Yeah.

187
00:10:40,645 --> 00:10:45,545
"Moji Retro Town."

188
00:10:47,545 --> 00:10:50,045
"Moji Harbor Train Station."

189
00:10:52,845 --> 00:10:55,844
This ferry takes only five minutes

190
00:10:55,845 --> 00:10:58,444
and even if you go through that tunnel we took and walked slowly,

191
00:10:58,445 --> 00:11:00,444
it takes only 15 minutes one way.

192
00:11:00,445 --> 00:11:04,544
Honshu and Kyushu are very close, aren't they?

193
00:11:04,545 --> 00:11:08,844
This is one of those things you can't tell just by looking at maps.

194
00:11:08,845 --> 00:11:09,945
Yeah.

195
00:11:16,045 --> 00:11:19,544
The locals call balloon fish "fuku" instead of "fugu"?

196
00:11:19,545 --> 00:11:21,944
Yes. Fuku, not fugu.

197
00:11:21,945 --> 00:11:23,944
I see.

198
00:11:23,945 --> 00:11:25,945
"Fuku" for happiness.

199
00:11:27,145 --> 00:11:29,744
Your father's so funny.

200
00:11:29,745 --> 00:11:31,245
Excuse me.

201
00:11:35,045 --> 00:11:36,245
Hario.

202
00:11:38,145 --> 00:11:42,344
Akitaya, give your company up.

203
00:11:42,345 --> 00:11:43,744
You tell me to give it up?

204
00:11:43,745 --> 00:11:48,444
I'm a consultant for a food manufacturer now.

205
00:11:48,445 --> 00:11:52,645
They told me they want to buy your company.

206
00:11:54,745 --> 00:11:57,244
They'll pay good money.

207
00:11:57,245 --> 00:11:59,444
Sounds like a fair deal, don't you think?

208
00:11:59,445 --> 00:12:01,344
You've got to be kidding.

209
00:12:01,345 --> 00:12:04,744
My father started the company and he worked hard for it.

210
00:12:04,745 --> 00:12:07,045
I'm not letting go of it so easily.

211
00:12:08,645 --> 00:12:12,044
I could crush your company right now if I wanted to.

212
00:12:12,045 --> 00:12:14,844
You're nothing, you're just garbage.

213
00:12:14,845 --> 00:12:17,144
What'd you say?

214
00:12:17,145 --> 00:12:19,844
Enjoy yourself tonight.

215
00:12:19,845 --> 00:12:22,145
I'll contact you tomorrow.

216
00:12:23,245 --> 00:12:25,345
Hario, wait.

217
00:12:26,845 --> 00:12:30,444
Did you come back to Shimonoseki to tell him that?

218
00:12:30,445 --> 00:12:34,045
Didn't you come for Hondo's memorial service?

219
00:12:37,845 --> 00:12:40,145
Who's that? I don't know anyone named Hondo.

220
00:12:47,145 --> 00:12:48,544
Hario!

221
00:12:48,545 --> 00:12:51,144
Hey! Wait, Hario!

222
00:12:51,145 --> 00:12:53,644
Have you no heart? Answer me, Hario.

223
00:12:53,645 --> 00:12:55,644
Apologize to Eiko.

224
00:12:55,645 --> 00:12:57,845
Don't touch me with your filthy hands.

225
00:13:00,045 --> 00:13:01,744
Otsubo.

226
00:13:01,745 --> 00:13:04,544
I don't know what you're talking about.

227
00:13:04,545 --> 00:13:05,844
Are you alright?

228
00:13:05,845 --> 00:13:07,145
Darn.

229
00:13:12,145 --> 00:13:14,744
He's so mean... so mean.

230
00:13:14,745 --> 00:13:16,045
Eiko.

231
00:13:28,411 --> 00:13:29,510
"Next day."

232
00:13:29,511 --> 00:13:31,810
They're all such nice people, that's why...

233
00:13:31,811 --> 00:13:33,711
"Former Akita Company" -I kind of, feel sorry for them.

234
00:13:35,611 --> 00:13:37,310
You mean Mr. Akitaya and his friends?

235
00:13:37,311 --> 00:13:42,110
Yes, but there's nothing we can do to help.

236
00:13:42,111 --> 00:13:43,810
Hey, you two!

237
00:13:43,811 --> 00:13:47,810
I just found out it's a 15 minute bus ride to Chofu from here.

238
00:13:47,811 --> 00:13:50,710
Do we have to go to that "Mouri Residence"?

239
00:13:50,711 --> 00:13:52,110
Of course we do.

240
00:13:52,111 --> 00:13:55,010
The famous Motonari Mouri is my ancestor,

241
00:13:55,011 --> 00:13:56,810
his descendant lives there.

242
00:13:56,811 --> 00:14:00,710
Are you really related to the famous Motonari Mouri?

243
00:14:00,711 --> 00:14:03,011
I heard this the first time today.

244
00:14:04,111 --> 00:14:05,411
I thought so.

245
00:14:10,411 --> 00:14:12,711
I wonder if there was an accident or something.

246
00:14:17,811 --> 00:14:20,111
I guess my ancestor will have to wait.

247
00:14:31,011 --> 00:14:33,610
The victim's driver's license.

248
00:14:33,611 --> 00:14:37,210
Seiji Hario, 30 years old, the address is in Tokyo.

249
00:14:37,211 --> 00:14:39,210
Did you say Hario?

250
00:14:39,211 --> 00:14:40,510
-It can't be... -It can't be...

251
00:14:40,511 --> 00:14:42,610
Who are you?

252
00:14:42,611 --> 00:14:46,410
The name's Kogoro Mouri, I'm a private detective in Tokyo.

253
00:14:46,411 --> 00:14:48,810
Mouri, the famous private detective.

254
00:14:48,811 --> 00:14:50,010
Yes, I suppose I am.

255
00:14:50,011 --> 00:14:52,010
I've heard all about you.

256
00:14:52,011 --> 00:14:54,610
I'm Kusuda with the Yamaguchi Prefectural Police.

257
00:14:54,611 --> 00:14:57,111
I'm Anzai with the Shimonoseki Police Department.

258
00:14:59,811 --> 00:15:02,910
You seem to recognize the victim.

259
00:15:02,911 --> 00:15:06,210
Yes, sort of...

260
00:15:06,211 --> 00:15:10,610
He died of a cerebral contusion caused by a blow to the back of the head.

261
00:15:10,611 --> 00:15:12,810
The murder weapon appears to be this rock

262
00:15:12,811 --> 00:15:15,310
but we may not be able to get any fingerprints off of it.

263
00:15:15,311 --> 00:15:20,611
Approximate time of death is between 9 am and 1 pm or thereabouts.

264
00:15:25,011 --> 00:15:27,510
They've been scraped on the ground pretty hard.

